Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.81,0:00:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.76,0:00:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light so glaring that it can't be hidden shatters the silence and revives in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The violently quaking and thirsty Earth stakes its life and clashes together with sparks
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.53,0:00:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just one more time is enough to create a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.75,0:00:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the power to regain the pages of memory lost in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.67,0:00:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\fs30}The believing heart that penetrates the darkness searches for the place where its soul sleeps
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.97,0:01:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And burns a sharp glance of eyes that can't sparkle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.35,0:01:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Two hearts of light and shadow head toward the future that the crystal reflects
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.69,0:01:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now they start to move, these eyes brimming red
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.79,0:01:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The other me is starting on his journey to search for his lost memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.12,0:01:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's finally time to reveal the memories of three thousand years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.26,0:01:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What kind of fate lies ahead for us when that happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:01:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the God Cards were stolen before we set off on our trip to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.68,0:01:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah! You're Bakura-{\i0}kun{\i1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.34,0:01:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dark Bakura on the Move"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.93,0:02:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're... Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single soul out there not aware that you have the God Cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.58,0:02:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural that these people would want to steal them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it {\i1}your duty{\i0} to protect them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And these {\i1}wretched losers{\i0}, of all people...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.29,0:02:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga-{\i1}kun{\i0} and Ryuzaki-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.62,0:02:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a close shave!\N You'd nearly lost them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cards are safe...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.34,0:02:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talking about {\i1}this{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.11,0:02:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you'll need to lend this to me for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.76,0:02:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was something that belonged to {\i1}me{\i0} originally, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.63,0:02:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.72,0:02:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the dark personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.98,0:02:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But rest assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:03:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the Millennium Items are necessary When the Pharaoh regains his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.23,0:03:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return this to you when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.04,0:03:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How much does Bakura-{\i0}kun{\i1} know about the Millennium Items?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.24,0:03:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the Tablet of the Pharaoh's Memories is in an underground temple in Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.09,0:03:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that it has holes in it that match the Millennium Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.84,0:03:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}, do you {\i1}know{\i0} about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what happens when you fit all the Millennium Items into the tablet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.38,0:03:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. You mean the Slate of Memories located in the village of Kul Elna?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That stone tablet is an artifact that connects {\i1}this{\i0} world to the world {\i1}beyond{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It links our world to the world beyond?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the seven Millennium Items are placed in the stone tablet...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.78,0:03:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Door of the Underworld will open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.25,0:03:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Door of the Underworld...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My real aim is what lies {\i0}beyond{\i1} that door...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.10,0:03:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To open the door to the afterlife...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.04,0:04:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.65,0:04:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Millennium Puzzle has sealed up the soul of the other me-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the Pharaoh's soul will return back to the afterlife, or the "Underworld".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} is your mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.13,0:04:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you out however I can, if it means accomplishing that mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0}, just what are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.99,0:04:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura, what are you plotting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, his majesty shows himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried about that I'd trick that vessel of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.17,0:04:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.70,0:04:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the same as you, a soul that was sealed 3,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your {\i1}true{\i0} identity?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me. I can't remember {\i1}that much{\i0} about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.25,0:04:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the answer to that may be somewhere in your memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:05:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say, Your Highness?\N Isn't it about time we settled things?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On a stage most fitting for us...\N Your Memory World.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.26,0:05:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My "Memory World"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't know anything about yourself, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.41,0:05:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That impenetrable maze in your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.79,0:05:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The complex games filled with mystery you continue to involve yourself with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.13,0:05:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we trace those mysteries to the root source,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.05,0:05:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it all points in the direction\N of your Memory World.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.90,0:05:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the Ultimate Dark Game is lying in wait there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.60,0:05:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ultimate Dark Game?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may not remember a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you were the one\N who started that game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who started the Dark Game?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.08,0:05:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why it is the most fitting place for us to finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.07,0:05:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ultimate Dark Game...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Memory World...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, Bakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.67,0:05:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accept your challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.89,0:05:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the door to your memory opens, the game will start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to the moment it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now then, there are still some things that I need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Prior preparations that I need in order to win the Ultimate Dark Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.40,0:06:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, President!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thanks for working overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.20,0:06:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Bakura...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mo-Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.28,0:06:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't worry, he's only unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you up to, you bastard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing, this is just a greeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.86,0:06:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanted to have a Dark Game with you up on the big stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How about a Duel, Seto-{\i0}sama{\i1}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, President.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.12,0:07:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, shall we start the Dark Game?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Game? What nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.95,0:07:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For such a pathetic reason, you went after Mokuba...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.45,0:07:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's when your luck ran out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.97,0:07:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare think that you'll leave here unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.49,0:07:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll regret this, you cretin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's with this heavy, painful atmosphere?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the game you often experienced 3,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A game from 3,000 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.28,0:08:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone like me who always looks ahead, today's victory belongs to yesterday's glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.73,0:08:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here to talk about ridiculous occult bullshit, go find Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.78,0:08:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.... Yugi is also joining this Dark Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.89,0:08:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What lies ahead for me and Yugi is the Ultimate Dark Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.26,0:08:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For that purpose, I must be wary of all risks and dangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.48,0:08:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You see, a Monster capable of destroying the gods lies within your deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start! I'll go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.49,0:08:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.01,0:08:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fuse Headless Knight and Ghost Earl from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Summon The Dead Duke!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't attack on my first turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:09:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.09,0:09:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph. So, you Summoned a Monster with an Attack of 2000 in the first turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Blood Vorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that guy's Attack Points aren't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.83,0:09:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Shrink!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.45,0:09:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will reduce the Attack Power of one Monster on the field by half.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Blood Vorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Monster is one that cannot be destroyed in battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But rather than protect you, it will become your downfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.01,0:09:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and do it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.08,0:09:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that, I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.66,0:09:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.47,0:09:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that Monster around, your Life should go down by 500 points each turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:09:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to skip that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know some pretty trivial crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice The Dead Duke to Summon Diabound Kernel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I activate the Equipment Magic, Spirit Illusion, from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Equipment Card allows me to Special Summon a Doppelganger Token
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.63,0:10:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the same attributes as the Monster equipped with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of how many weaklings you play, nothing will change here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.36,0:10:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Doppelganger Diabound!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.98,0:10:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doppelganger Diabound has Special Abilities as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.92,0:10:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack Power of the Monster equipped
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with Doppelganger Diabound will have its Attack Power reduced by its own Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that, your Monster's Attack Power is only 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.21,0:10:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this, Seto!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card, and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.33,0:11:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.34,0:11:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Lord of Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Lord of Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.09,0:11:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this card is on the field face-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon-Types cannot be targeted by Magic or Trap Cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.07,0:11:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate a Magic Card, The Flute of Summoning Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.92,0:11:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Lord of Dragons is on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.24,0:11:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can call up to two Dragon-Types to the field from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.85,0:11:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.80,0:11:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The strongest creature lying in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My strongest and most beautiful servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.80,0:11:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So you've finally appeared, blue-eyed white dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The only Monster capable of going up against God!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.02,0:12:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was... that vision just now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The two gods\N have the same Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.78,0:12:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.69,0:13:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fog's engulfed the town...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.41,0:13:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this painful feeling...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was the vision that both Yugi and I saw when the two gods battled!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.01,0:13:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.94,0:13:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.54,0:13:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of trying to find out the reason, defeating this guy is more important now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:13:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.45,0:14:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.60,0:14:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.88,0:14:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, Spirit Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pity!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.92,0:14:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit Shield allows me to remove
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one Fiend-Type or Undead-Type from the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to negate a Monster's attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this effect continues as long as I have the Monsters needed for the cost in my Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.19,0:14:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, I'm safe for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.93,0:14:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Petty tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.73,0:14:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card face-down and complete my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.58,0:14:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.22,0:14:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't defeat him, I can't achieve my aim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Pot of Greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.75,0:14:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card's effect allows me to draw two cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then activate another Magic Card! Grief Tablet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord of Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the abilities of the Monster trapped in that stone slab will be sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.34,0:15:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need to destroy it with your own hands if you want to get out of this predicament!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.21,0:15:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that would mean losing 500 Life Points in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Doppelganger Token!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go get Blue-Eyes!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Diabound Kernel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.45,0:15:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Death Spiral!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.15,0:15:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate my Trap!\N Attack Guidance Armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.46,0:15:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.15,0:15:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two cards and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.08,0:15:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:15:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This man certainly did his research on my deck...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That just means that I'll be the {\i0}true{\i1} victor if I can win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the sake of my deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.57,0:16:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the sake of my Blue-Eyes..!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.12,0:16:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Life-Shaving Card Treasure, from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw until I have five cards in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.74,0:16:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After five turns, I must discard all the cards in my hand to the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.17,0:16:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter what cards you draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because I have the invincible Spirit Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.71,0:16:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll destroy that shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.30,0:16:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, Soul Release!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.97,0:16:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With its effects, Ghost Earl and The Death Duke are excluded from your Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've lost all the Fiend-Type and Undead Zombie-Type Monsters in your Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.19,0:16:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that, your shield is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.84,0:16:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I activate the Magic Card, Silent Death, from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Special Summon Blood Vorse back from my Graveyard in Attack Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then sacrifice Blood Vorse and Blue-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.02,0:16:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.91,0:17:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rather than let you live on in that weak state, I'll let you be reborn in a new life!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.64,0:17:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sacrificed your Blue-Eyes to Summon another Blue-Eyes White Dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The likes of {\i1}you{\i0} has no business touching my Blue-Eyes like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.51,0:17:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.43,0:17:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Trap! Mirror Tablet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.41,0:17:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate another Trap, Rebirth Tablet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.70,0:17:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.87,0:17:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebirth Tablet is a Trap Card activated when a Monster is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.88,0:17:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It allows me to revive a Monster in my Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.93,0:17:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:18:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Monster is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mirror Tablet transfers half of the Attack Power of the destroyed Monster to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.37,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The selected Monster is then forced into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.05,0:18:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the Attack Power of Diabound Kernel is higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.93,0:18:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go forth, Diabound Kernel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.32,0:18:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Death Spiral!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.00,0:18:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes is {\i1}immortal{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.09,0:18:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, Resurrection of the Dead!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.82,0:18:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The {\i0}true{\i1} Special Ability of Diabound...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.04,0:18:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It holds the power to absorb the abilities of the Monsters it defeats.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.72,0:18:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For now, my goal has been fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.58,0:18:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already this time...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pity, Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave it at that for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.40,0:18:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You plan to leave in the middle of a Duel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to head out on a trip, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give {\i1}this{\i0} to you to make up for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.15,0:19:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus'...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, the Millennium Eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your invitation to the Ultimate Dark Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to settle this, take that with you and come to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.07,0:19:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Egypt{\i0}? What nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep saying it! I have {\i1}no interest{\i0} in all this ludicrous occult business!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.25,0:19:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you at least a {\i1}bit interested{\i0} in the connection between you and Blue-Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.93,0:19:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me and Blue-Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.35,0:19:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be eagerly waiting for you, Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.41,0:20:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The connection between me and Blue-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.53,0:20:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Hey~!\N -Hey~!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.33,0:20:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.27,0:20:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Anzu! Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}! All that luggage...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.21,0:20:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.90,0:20:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading to Egypt too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you worry about the expenses... Anzu will be paying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only lending you some of the funds I'll be using to study overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.48,0:20:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, Miss! I swear to work hard and pay you back when we return!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.81,0:20:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to beg my big sis for the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we can't possibly just send you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.99,0:21:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Besides, the other Yugi is our friend too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.44,0:21:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That about sums it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.53,0:21:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.71,0:21:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Let's head to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.42,0:21:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's finally time to open the door to my Memory World.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.40,0:21:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And when that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.84,0:21:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the Ultimate Dark Game between Bakura and me will start as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.43,0:22:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To show us now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.73,0:22:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...a map isn't needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Only what tore apart the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.33,0:22:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...the hope that lies in my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.46,0:22:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Without deciding on a goal...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.89,0:22:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll just take a step toward my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.52,0:22:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}EYE'S, while I feel them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.98,0:22:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll find your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.62,0:22:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh! EYE'S, if what I wished for...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.83,0:23:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...shudders my very soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.38,0:23:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...a Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.38,0:23:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we must go together to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this way of sending the other Yugi off in search of his memory just doesn't seem right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.19,0:23:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, after this, the other Yugi may...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.49,0:23:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can't get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.99,0:23:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is his greatest wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must bid him a joyful farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.21,0:23:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with Ishizu-{\i1}san{\i0} and her family, who were waiting for us in Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.59,0:23:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we finally head off for the Memory Tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.19,0:23:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.77,0:23:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Door of Memory Opens"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.77,0:23:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look forward to it!
